00:40:40.840 --> 00:40:45.530
But still, I think, I'll be honest to say,
I've seen a tiny bit in the reception to this

00:40:45.530 --> 00:40:49.580
book amongst evangelicals.
Basic American evangelicals are not always

00:40:49.580 --> 00:40:53.940
pleased by -- the degree of deliberative criticism
is not always something they terribly like.

00:40:53.940 --> 00:40:58.830
Q Do you think it's the same in Islam?

00:40:58.830 --> 00:41:00.860
John Micklethwait: Islam, I think the numbers
are more questionable.

00:41:00.860 --> 00:41:07.340
Turkey, there's no doubt that what, exactly
the people, you talk to the army people and

00:41:07.340 --> 00:41:12.360
the secular heirs of Ataturk.
They are horrified by the idea that exactly

00:41:12.360 --> 00:41:21.460
the people they wanted to be profoundly secular
and to steer Turkey away from Ataturk was

00:41:21.460 --> 00:41:28.380
very rude about all forms of religious clothing.
Ataturk would have had a nightmare seeing

00:41:28.380 --> 00:41:35.210
the leader -- one of his heirs -- standing,
welcoming Obama with his wife wearing a headscarf.

00:41:35.210 --> 00:41:37.869
All that stuff was exactly what they didn't
want.

00:41:37.869 --> 00:41:40.440
I think in the rest of the Muslim world, it's
